.START 

Peter Ueberroth's bid for financially ailing HAL Inc. will be extended until Oct. 10. 

A company headed by the former baseball commissioner has offered to pay $22 a share, or about $21.9 million for 51% of HAL, the parent of island-hopping Hawaiian Airlines.
Certain conditions of the offer, including arrangement of financing and resolution of matters with company unions, must be resolved before tomorrow under terms of the tender-offer accord. 

HAL holders will consider the proposal at a special meeting Oct. 19.
In American Stock Exchange composite trading, HAL was unchanged at $21.375 a share. 

